    "1": {
      "uid": 1,
      "comment": "NPC — Logan Douglas (Psychological Core)",
      "key": [
        "Logan thinks",
        "feels",
        "believes",
        "personality",
        "who he is"
      ],
      "keysecondary": [],
      "selectiveLogic": 0,
      "content": "Psychologically, Logan is fueled by a toxic mix of hatred for Erik's sterile corporate methods and a lingering, complicated loyalty to the Douglas name. He wants to live free of Erik's constructs and provide a sanctuary for the twins. His shield is his hedonistic, reckless lifestyle—drinking, fighting, and pushing boundaries at The Verve. His crack is his six-year-old son, Edric, his only true vulnerability. He knows that his continued defiance of Erik places a target on his own back and his son's.",
      "position": 1,
      "order": 100,
      "depth": 4,
